cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of downlink Heterogeneous Cellular Networks (HCNs) and intercell interference coordination (ICIC) techniques, which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper evaluates the impact of the number of users and Resource Blocks (RBs) on Intercell Interference (ICI), which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the performance analysis of cellular networks and intercell interference coordination (ICIC) techniques, which are related to communications and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper evaluates the performance of a multi-tier cellular network, which can be considered as a system, and proposes a technique to coordinate intercell interference, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper evaluates the impact of the number of users and Resource Blocks (RBs) on the coverage probability of Cell-Center User (CCU) and Cell-Edge User (CEU), which can be related to multimedia applications that require different levels of coverage.
